cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about weakly-supervised semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel self-guided strategy that utilizes features learned across multiple levels to generate dense pseudo labels. This involves training a neural network, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method to refine the localization maps, which could fall under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses the PASCAL VOC 2012 segmentation benchmark for evaluation, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's use of a single network for the entire process could also place it in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
